ires from John Prine\n* [[Reverend Musical Instruments|Reverend]] Buckshot\n* Reverend Flatroc w/ Les Trem\n* [[Harmony Company|Harmony]] Archtop<ref name=HearYa-2011>{{cite web|last=Oz|title=An Interview With Jason Isbell \u2013 Here We Rest.|url=http://www.hearya.com/2011/04/05/an-interview-with-jason-isbell-here-we-rest/|work=Hear Ya|accessdate=27 March 2014|date=5 April 2011}}</ref>\n* Fender Telecaster\n\n===Amps===\n* [[Fender Musical Instruments Corporation|Fender]] [[Vibroverb]]\n* [[Fender Musical Instruments Corporation|Fender]] Princeton\n*Fender Deluxe Reverb\n* Fender pro (non-reverb)\n* Sommatone Roaring-40 head and 2x12 cabinet\n* [[Magnatone]] Super Fifty-Nine\n* [[Tone King]] Imperial MKII\n* [[Vox (musical equipment)|Vox]] AC30HW\n\n===Other gear===\n* Marion Henry Guitar pedals\n* Mr. B's Bottleneck Guitar slides\n* POG electro-harmonix octave generator<ref name=HearYa-2011/>\n* Klon Centaur\n* [[Z.Vex Effects|Z.Vex]] Box of Rock overdrive pedal<ref name=HearYa-2011/>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===[[Americana Music Honors & Awards]]===\nThe [[Americana Music Honors & Awards]] celebrate outstanding achievement in the genre of Americana. Isbell has won nine awards out of 16 nominations.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Category !! Nominated Work !! Result\n|-\n| 2009 || Album of the Year || ''[[Jason Isbell and The 400 Unit]]'' || {{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2012 ||  Song of the Year || \"Alabama Pines\" || {{Won}}\n|-\n| Album of the Year || ''[[Here We Rest]]'' || {{Nom}}\n|-\n| Artist of the Year || Jason Isbell || {{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2014 || Song of the Year || \"Cover Me Up\" || {{Won}}\n|-\n| Album of the Year || [[Southeastern (album)|''Southeastern'']] || {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|Artist of the Year || rowspan=2|Jason Isbell || {{Won}}\n|-\n| 2015 || {{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2016 || Album of the Year || ''[[Something More Than Free]]'' || {{Won}}\n|-\n| Song of the Year || \"24 Frames\" || {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|Artist of the Ye