ard for Best Americana Album|Best Americana Album]]|| ''[[Something More Than Free]]'' || {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[60th Annual Grammy Awards|2018]] || [[Grammy Award for Best American Roots Song|Best American Roots Song]] || \"If We Were Vampires\" || {{won}} \n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Americana Album|Best Americana Album]]|| ''[[The Nashville Sound]]'' || {{won}}\n|}\n\n===[[Americana Music Honors & Awards|UK Americana Awards]]===\nThe [[Americana Music Honors & Awards|UK Americana Awards]] celebrate the best roots music released in the UK and internationally. Isbell has received two nomination.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.entertainment-focus.com/music-section/music-news/robert-plant-to-receive-lifetime-achievement-award-at-uk-americana-awards-2018/|title=Robert Plant to receive Lifetime Achievement Award at UK Americana Awards 2018 - Entertainment Focus|website=Entertainment-focus.com}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Category !! Nominated Work !! Result\n|-\n|2018 || International Album of the Year || ''[[The Nashville Sound]]'' || {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2016 || International Artist of the Year || ''Jason Isbell'' || {{Won}}\n|}\n\n==Home media==\n* Weissman, Barr, Patterson Hood, Mike Cooley, Shonna Tucker, Brad Morgan, [[John Neff (Musician)|John Neff]], and Jason Isbell. ''[http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/709937022 The Secret to a Happy Ending: A Documentary About the Drive-by Truckers.]'' New York: ATO Records, 2011. (DVD of 2009 documentary)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Drive-By Truckers]]\n* [[Muscle Shoals Sound Studio]]\n* [[Muscle Shoals, Alabama]]\n* [[Amanda Shires]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Jason Isbell}}\n* [http://www.jasonisbell.com JasonIsbell.com] (official site)\n\n{{Jason Isbell}}\n{{Drive-By Truckers}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Isbell, Jason}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lauderdale County, Alabam